The major event, according to the organisers, will be held at the Tumaini Makumira University grounds, at Usa-River section of Meru District in the next six months time.The Church Spokesperson, Mrs Elizabeth Lobulu stated that the 500 years of Church Reformation will be observed by all believers in the country this year but the actual climax ceremony is scheduled for October 2017.Christendom Church Reformation was started in Germany by Martin Luther in 1517 who led the split from the main Catholic Church then and spearheaded the creation of the Lutheran Church globally and the Protestant movement.Mrs Lobulu, quoting the ELCT Secretary General, Mr Brighton Killewa, said the Reformation Week programme will start on October 1, 2017, with many activities conducted in all ELCT parishes, institutions, dioceses and at national level.